{{unreferenced|date=October 2018}} Panama's national public holidays are:
* January 1, [[New Year's Day]] * January 9, [[Martyrs' Day (Panama)|Martyrs' Day]] * [[Caribbean Carnival|Carnival]]'s Monday. The Monday before [[Ash Wednesday]]. * Carnival's Tuesday. The Tuesday before [[Ash Wednesday]]. * Holy Friday - [[Good Friday]] - Death of Christ * May 1, [[May Day]] - Labor Day * July 1. (every 5 years) presidential inauguration * November 2. [[Day of the Dead]] {{cn|date=November 2017}} * November 3. Separation Day (from [[Colombia]]). * November 4. [[Flag of Panama|Flag Day]] * November 5. [[Colón, Panama|Colón Day]] * November 10. "Primer Grito de Independencia de la Villa de los Santos" celebrating [[The Gesture of Rufina Alfaro]] and the uprising in the [[Villa de los Santos]] against Spain. * November 28. [[Independence Day]] (from [[Spain]]). * December 8. [[Mothers' Day]]. * December 24.[[Christmas Eve]]. * December 25. [[Christmas]].
The holidays in November (starting from Separation Day), are called the Fiestas Patrias ("Patriotic Holidays").<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.panama-offshore-services.com/blog/fiestas_patrias_panama_celebrates_its_history_all_through_november.htm |title=Fiestas Patrias: Panama celebrates its history all through November |last=Chatlani |first=Manoj |date=2014-11-07 |website=POLS - Attorneys |language=en-US |access-date=2018-11-02 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>
