[[File:Alonso Messia SJ, Devotion a la tres horas.JPG|thumb|Front page of the ''Devotion a la tres horas'' by P. Alonso Messia SJ.]]
The '''Three Hours' Agony''', ''"Tre Ore"''.<!-- source: http://www.fisheaters.com/customslent14.html Good Friday] at fisheaters.org -- for some reason that website is blacklisted on wiki, so can't add that as a live link--> '''The Great Three Hours''', or '''Three Hours' Devotion''' is a service held in some [[Roman Catholic]], [[Anglican]], and [[Lutheran]] [[Christian Church|church]]es on [[Good Friday]] from noon till 3 o'clock to commemorate the [[Passion (Christianity)|Passion of Christ]].
It may include meditation on the seven [[sayings of Jesus on the cross]],<ref>[http://www.catholicculture.org/culture/library/view.cfm?id=2719&repos=1&subrepos=0&searchid=1619157 Sermons on the Three Hours’ Agony] at CatholicCulture.org</ref> and often occurs between the [[Stations of the Cross]] at noon and the [[Good Friday#Liturgy|Liturgy of the Lord's Passion]] at 3PM, or between 6PM and 9PM.<ref>[https://books.google.pl/books?id=Hj4_uC-57wMC&pg=PA1&dq=tre+ore&hl=pl&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwic_7TRoo7MAhVPb5oKHff5DK8Q6AEIUjAJ#v=onepage&q=tre%20ore&f=false Divozione alle tre ore dell'agonia di Gesù Cristo nostro redentore...]</ref>
The [[Jesuit]] priest Alphonsus Messia (died 1732) is said to have devised this devotion in [[Lima]], Peru. It was introduced to Rome around 1788 and spread around the world. In 1815, [[Pope Pius VII]] decreed a plenary [[indulgence]] to those who practise this devotion on Good Friday.<ref>[http://members.aol.com/liturgialatina/raccolta/crucified.htm#30 Raccolta - Jesus Crucified<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>
